<paragraph blockId="56.[2065,2658,1741,2165]" pageId="56" pageNumber="814">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Jentink" authorityYear="1890" box="[2066,2352,1816,1849]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Hypsugo" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="56" pageNumber="814" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="vordermanni">Hypsugo vordermanni</taxonomicName>
appears to be closely related to 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Temminck" baseAuthorityYear="1840" box="[2219,2371,1860,1889]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Hypsugo" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="56" pageNumber="814" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="macrotis">H. macrotis</taxonomicName>
, to which it is morphologically very similar. Monotypic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
